briefdescription.para: Macro to force the compiler to always inline an inline function.

detaileddescription.para: GCC: in GCC, the inline keyword is not always regarded by the compiler. Based on the situation the compiler can decide to emit a real function instead of the function body only. Defining a function as always_inline makes it madatory for the compiler to inline it always.

simplesect.para: Inlining makes C level debugging hard as the inlined code is not aligned with the source file. To eliminate this issue, in debug builds the macro is disabled.

briefdescription.para: Macro to inform the compiler that a variable is intentionally not in use.
Macro to inform the compiler that a function is intentionally not in use.

detaileddescription.para:
GCC: in GCC the compiler option -Wunused (-Wall) generates warnings if a function is not in use. Using the BCDS_UNUSED_FUNC() macro results in the following changes in compiler behavior:
attached to a function, the macro means that the function is meant to be possibly unused. GCC will not produce a warning for this function.

parameterdescription.para: : The unused function with its arguments list.
